# Git attribution — no Cursor trailers

- Never append `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Made-with: Cursor`, or any Cursor / Anthropic / assistant attribution line to **git commits**, **merge commits**, or **PR descriptions**.
- When creating commits from this workspace, use normal `git commit` with a clean message body, or low-level `git write-tree` + `git commit-tree` if the tooling would otherwise inject trailers — never leave Cursor listed as co-author.
- If the user asks to push: verify `git log -1 --format=%B` contains no `Co-authored-by:` line for Cursor before pushing.
